				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">True Newbie question<a name="17398"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 11:22 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Obviously I am not afraid of using this term because that is exactly what I am. I've been playing for about 3 weeks and I have a 15 lvl half elf bard on Kane bayle. I came over from EQOA (ps2) where I played a 55 lvl bard. I am soooo glad I switched because the depth and gameplay is not even close to the pc version. I guess the only problem I am having is finding groups. Being that the game is older and my server is older there are not alot of newbies to grp with. I have a buddy that has a lvl 40 pally and 38 warrior but plays a 12 wizard with me so that's my daily duo. Either way here is the point of my ranting....
<br />
When I bought the game I purchased all the expansions and an atlas (IMPORTANT!!! IF YOU ARE A NEWBIE BUY THE ATLAS!) which has saved me tons of travel time. BUT..... I hit 15 and I see 2 songs available to me. One I bought but the other is a song for food i guess? How does this song work? Will I ever need to buy food again? And can this song be purchased in the POK library? The help guide that lists song locations references a zone both me and my buddy are unfamiliar with. My fear is that I will do a run for a worthless song that may get me killed and make my body unexcessible even to my buddy's pally. Any advice is appreciated. 
<br />

<br />
BTW if you are a true (untwinked) newbie like my guy this is all the advice I have beside buying the atlas.
<br />
At lvl 11 till now I have fought/farmed xp and good money off of wisps (they drop Greater Lightstones sometimes) in east commons and then selling them for a research box to a gypsy in north karanna. Wisps drop lightstones and greater lightstones. (NOTE::Greater ones are the ones you want but regular lightstones will sell for 9 gold so there not too bad either.) Then you turn around and sell the research box back to the gypsy for 9 plat+. The gypsy's name is Myra I beleive.  
<br />
Secondly, if you start in Kelethin like i did the armor quests are easy except for the boots. For the boots what I did was go to Freeport and do the bard newbie armor quest for the boots, much easier same stats. 
<br />

<br />
Tarelus 15th bard
<br />
&quot;We want the funk!!!&quot;   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
