			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: True Newbie question<a name="23821"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 12:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As you're on an older server and instruments should be pretty cheap in the bazaar there's no real reason to head off to Katta Castellum until about Level 30.
<br />

<br />
If on the other hand you're on a new server a Combine Drum and Lute may be the best instruments you'll be able to get for quite a while and they're for sale in Katta.  With a 2.2 modifier (regular store bought instruments are 1.8) they make a big difference with Healing and Speed Songs.  Chords of Dissonance are also a lot more effective with a good lute in hand.
<br />

<br />
On a new server, I'll start hunting Gopher Snakes in the Qeynos yard.  Some of the items they drop sell for a couple of gold and they stack. There are a lot of them there and you can easily make several pp for songs and gear before you hit Level 3.  From there I hunt Goblins and Large Skunks in Butcherblock as soon as I can.  The Skunks are Level 2 and drop Pristine Claws that sell for about 1.5pp (been a price drop recently) while the Goblins drop Heads and Vials of Blood that sell for 4pp.
<br />

<br />
Another good source for cash, but it depends on you finding another player looking for tailoring components, is to hunt the Young Lions and Young Lionesses near the second guard tower in from the Qeynos Hills in the West Karanas.  These are currently dropping HQ cat skins if they drop any skin at all and these will sell for about 10pp on an older server.  While you're in the West Karanas if you kill any bandits keep an eye out for Bandit Sashes.  You can turn these in to Chesgard in the South Qeynos Paladin guild in return for faction and a Bronze weapon that you can sell for a couple of pp.
<br />

<br />
Once I have about 120 pp saved up (usually around Level 9) I head off to Katta Castellum to get my Drum and Lute.  Since I know the route from having travelled it as a high level it's not terribly dangerous so long as I keep the drum song going and zig zag around any mobs I see.  Check EQAtlas for printable zone maps for Hollowshade Moor (off of kittie city of Shar Vahl), The Grimling Forrest and the Tenebreous Mountains.
<br />

<br />
When you get to Katta from the Tenebreous Mountains entrance hug the wall to the right and the first building you come to has the merchants selling the songs and instruments.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
